From: AgentOS Runtime <runtime@agentos.invalid>
Subject: [PATCH] brush-parser: preserve heredocs when formatting functions

Brush uses formatted function definitions to restore the inherited function
environment in a real background child. Pretty-print indentation prefixes
here-document terminators with spaces, making the formatted definition invalid
for ordinary `<<` heredocs. Quoted delimiters have a second constraint: the
opening word retains its quotes while the closing tag is quote-removed. Shell
grammar does not require compound-command indentation, so keep bodies at column
zero, use their newline separators instead of appending a standalone semicolon
after a closing tag, and emit the parsed delimiter form required at each
location.

--- a/src/ast.rs
+++ b/src/ast.rs
@@ -5,8 +5,6 @@ use std::fmt::{Display, Write};
 
 use crate::{TokenLocation, tokenizer};
 
-const DISPLAY_INDENT: &str = "    ";
